OL,3,C'We want to contribute' - Asylum
OL,4,Cseekers share open letter on life in
OL,5,Chotels
OL,7,FThey wrote: "We do not want to be
OL,8,Fdependent on the British government
OL,9,Ffor support. We want to work and
OL,10,Fcontribute. But the government does
OL,11,Fnot allow us to work."
OL,13,FAccording to the Home Office, asylum
OL,14,Fseekers are generally not allowed to
OL,15,Fwork while their claim for asylum is
OL,16,Fbeing considered, at least for the
OL,17,Ffirst 12 months after submitting the
OL,18,Fclaim.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/12
